		<meta property="og:description" content="Dear Ross: How can you miss on purpose? If I&amp;rsquo;m late getting back on defense, you&amp;rsquo;ll bounce the ball off the bottom of the rim and catch the &amp;ldquo;rebound&amp;rdquo; for a point. Alone under the basket. Missing.

Dear Noah:&amp;nbsp;Bouncing the ball off the bottom of the rim is, as you say, a poorly missed shot, but also a perfectly missed one, because it results in a point in our game, which means it&amp;rsquo;s a way for me to stay on the court. If there were a way I could stay on the court without cheating &amp;mdash; without those perfectly, beautifully missed shots &amp;mdash; believe me, I would do it.">
